  "prompt": "Instagram (product): How do I quickly unfollow people on Instagram?",
  "response": "Here are a few ways to quickly unfollow people on Instagram:\n\n1. Desktop/Web Method:\n- Go to Instagram.com\n- Click on \"Following\" on your profile\n- Scroll through list and click \"Unfollow\" for each account\n- Faster than mobile app\n\n2. Mobile App Method:\n- Go to your profile\n- Tap \"Following\"\n- Tap \"Unfollow\" next to each account\n- Manually do this one-by-one\n\n3. Third-Party Apps (caution):\n- Some apps like Cleaner for Instagram can mass unfollow\n- Be careful of apps that might violate Instagram's terms of service\n- Risk of temporary account restriction\n\n4. Instagram's Native Bulk Unfollow (Limited):\n- No direct bulk unfollow feature\n- Must manually unfollow each account\n\n5. Advanced Method (for tech-savvy users):\n- Use browser extensions or scripts\n- Can automate unfollowing process\n- Higher risk of account penalties\n\nPro Tips:\n- Unfollow gradually to avoid Instagram's action blocks\n- Don't unfollow too many accounts too quickly\n- Consider using Instagram's \"Mute\" feature instead for less drastic action\n\nRecommended: Manual desktop or app method for safest approach.",
